dateRangeTime.tips: Friendly reminder: You can precisely control milliseconds through manual input!

MetricModel.measureNameRegular: Measure name must start with letters or numbers, only letters, numbers, and underscores allowed
MetricModel.metricModelNameRegular: Name must start with letters or numbers, only letters, numbers, and underscores allowed
MetricModel.measureNameTip: Name for the metric calculated by the metric model. When persistence task is configured, this field serves as the storage field for metric values. Must start with __m. and only letters, numbers, underscores are allowed for naming
MetricModel.formulaTip: The calculation formula defines the calculation rules for metrics. Please refer to the configuration instructions for metric model calculation formulas in the online help documentation.
MetricModel.measureFieldTip: When query language is DSL, metric field needs to be specified. Metric field is the aggregation name for value aggregation in DSL. Please refer to the configuration instructions for metric field in metric model in the online help documentation.
MetricModel.persistenceTaskNameTip: Persistence task name will be added as dimension task_name={name} to metric {measureName}. When creating metric model using current persisted data, need to add filter condition task_name={name}
MetricModel.timeWindowsTip: Time window refers to the time interval for metric data query. Only needs to be configured when query language is DSL. Time window configuration will be added as dimension {timeWindows} to metric {measureName}. When creating metric model using current persisted data, need to add {timeWindows} filter condition
MetricModel.indexBaseTip: Index base for persistent metric data writing
MetricModel.indexBaseInfo: If you cannot find the required index base, you can {new}
MetricModel.persistenceTaskDeleteConfirmTitle: Confirm to delete selected persistence task? This operation cannot be undone!
MetricModel.persistenceTaskStepTip: Time interval for metric data persistence generation. After configuring step, metric data persistence will generate data points at step intervals. Step configuration will be added as dimension {step} to metric {measureName}. When creating metric model using current persisted data, need to add {step} filter condition
MetricModel.stepFilterRepeat: Persistence step and filter conditions between tasks cannot be completely equal
MetricModel.isGroupDeleteForceDescription: If selected, metric models contained in the group will be deleted together; if not selected, cannot delete if there are metric models in the group
MetricModel.retraceDurationTip: Refers to using the time point after retracting the specified retrace duration from current time as the starting point for persistence. From the starting point, gradually calculate and persist metric data for each time point according to persistence step. Retraced data points = retrace duration/persistence step <= 10000
MetricModel.retraceDurationIsMax: Task's retraced data time points cannot exceed 10000. The current configured retrace duration {x} under minimum persistence step {y} results in {z} retraced data time points, which exceeds 10000.
MetricModel.idTip: ID is the unique identifier of the metric model, supports custom input. If not customized, system will generate automatically. Please note, once metric model creation is completed, ID cannot be changed.
MetricModel.cancelTip: Are you sure you want to cancel?
MetricModel.disabledBuiltGroupTip: Built-in groups do not allow editing, deleting, or exporting metric models within the group
MetricModel.disabledBuiltNewTip: Built-in metric models do not allow creation
MetricModel.disabledBuiltEditTip: Built-in metric models do not allow editing
MetricModel.disabledBuiltDeleteTip: Built-in metric models do not allow deletion
MetricModel.disabledBuiltImportTip: Built-in metric models do not allow importing
MetricModel.disabledBuiltExportTip: Built-in metric models do not allow exporting
MetricModel.disabledBuiltMoveTip: Built-in metric models do not allow moving
MetricModel.customIdTip: After enabling persistence configuration, highly readable ID will improve usability when using metric data in the future. Recommend custom ID input, or return to [Basic Configuration] step for custom input.
MetricModel.persistenceTaskNameCustomTip: Persistence task name will be added as dimension task_name={name} to system-generated metrics. When creating metric model using current persisted data, need to add filter condition task_name={name}
MetricModel.timeWindowsCustomTip: Time window refers to the time interval for metric data query. Only needs to be configured when query language is DSL. Time window configuration will be added as dimension {timeWindows} to system-generated metrics. When creating metric model using current persisted data, need to add {timeWindows} filter condition
MetricModel.persistenceTaskStepCustomTip: Time interval for metric data persistence generation. After configuring step, metric data persistence will generate data points at step intervals. Step configuration will be added as dimension {step} to system-generated metrics. When creating metric model using current persisted data, need to add {step} filter condition
MetricModel.currentModelNoPersistenceConfig: Current metric model has no persistence configuration, can skip this step to complete creation
MetricModel.formulaTip2: Please enter calculation formula, e.g.: name="zhansan"
MetricModel.formulaTip3: Please enter calculation formula, e.g.: count(field_name)
MetricModel.havingTip: When having is configured, having filtering is not performed for range query requests
MetricModel.youCanClickLeftSideToReference: You can click on atomic metrics, derived metrics, and composite metrics on the left to reference them in expressions
MetricModel.overwriteTip: Duplicate metric models detected, please select processing method
